Scenario: lead-po template carries a testable sufficiency criterion for the deep-research and requirements-elicitation research flavors
  When I read the lead-po template via "shop-templates show lead-po"
  Then the deep-research investigations flavor block states a sufficiency criterion that requires the investigation to be bounded — naming the question it set out to answer and stopping when answered
  And the deep-research investigations flavor block states a sufficiency criterion that requires the synthesis to be cited — the PDR rationale points at the evidence rather than at a hunch
  And the requirements-elicitation flavor block states a sufficiency criterion that requires each elicited requirement to trace back to a discovered problem and forward to at least one testable scenario
  And the requirements-elicitation flavor block does not replace or weaken the existing "Sufficiency check — authoring a scenario" section, but feeds well-formed scenarios into it
